Russian Sugar Trades for as Much as $1,221 a Ton, Producers Say

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-02-16T13:55:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-16/russian-sugar-trades-for-as-much-as-1-221-a-ton-producers-say.html
Russian sugar traded today at as
much as 33,700 rubles ($1,149) a metric ton in wholesale markets
in the Southern federal district and 35,800 rubles ($1,221) in
the Volga district, the country’s  Sugar Producers’ Union  said on
its website. The price was 34,300 rubles a ton in the Central
federal district, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow at 
 msysoyeva@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net . 